1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with video segmentation and visual features. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a discriminative-generative approach for learning and modelling the sub-activities. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with unsupervised learning and segmentation of complex activities. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with video analysis and segmentation. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with modelling the temporal structure of sub-activities.
